<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-illegiblecharapprox" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Illegible Characters, Quantity Approximate (Circa or Range)</head>
    <p><!--gloss--></p>
    <p><specList>
            <specDesc key="gap"/>
        </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p>

    <p>Where vestiges of characters remain, but they cannot be recognised and their quantity is
        approximate, they should be placed in a <gi>gap</gi> and given a <att>reason</att> with a
        value of "illegible", and either an attribute of <att>precision</att> with the value "low"
        (to express 'circa'), or a range of possible characters lost using <att>atLeast</att> and
            <att>atMost</att>.</p>

    <cit>
        <quote>[<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="superscript">c.5</hi></hi>]</quote>
        <bibl corresp="#panciera">
            <biblScope>VIII.3</biblScope>
        </bibl>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="5" unit="character" precision="low"/>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <gap reason="illegible" atLeast="4" atMost="6" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="london"
        corresp="http://inslib.kcl.ac.uk/irt2009/IRT560.html">
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="7" unit="character" precision="low"/>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="ddbdp"
        corresp="http://papyri.info/ddbdp/o.claud;4;844">
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="10" unit="character" precision="low"/>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="ddbdp"
        corresp="http://papyri.info/ddbdp/bgu;17;2683">
        <gap reason="illegible" atLeast="3" atMost="4" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>

    <divGen type="seealso"/>

